Correct classification — three tiers, not two:

TIER 1 — Confirmed Present (present = Yes):
Vendor batch-tests every batch per USP <469>, reports numeric result.
Signals in raw_text:
- "tested each batch" / "per-batch testing"
- Numeric CoA result column with value alongside spec
- "Result: X ppm" / "batch analysis"
- USP <469> per-batch testing statement
Table 2: Yes / Yes / numeric spec (e.g., "NMT 620 ppm")
Example: Polysorbate 80 Croda CoA

TIER 2 — Guarantee Ceiling (present = No, spec_limit populated):
Vendor guarantees below regulatory limit but does NOT test per batch.
Material on FDA high-risk list requires scientific rationale in Observations.
Signals in raw_text:
- "guarantee" / "guaranteed"
- "below Option 1" / "below Option 2"
- "not quantified per batch" / "not tested per batch"
- "less than" combined with regulatory reference
- Material on FDA high-risk list
- Vendor mechanism mentioned (e.g., "by-product of hydrogenation")
Table 2: No / No / numeric spec (e.g., "< 620 ppm" or "620 ppm (guarantee)")
Example: Mannitol Pearlitol 50C Roquette

TIER 3 — Not Present (present = No, spec_limit = "Not applicable"):
Manufacturing declaration, excluded by process, not tested, not mentioned.
Signals:
- "not used in manufacturing"
- "excluded by manufacturing process"
- "no source of DEG/EG"
- No DEG/EG mention at all
Table 2: No / No / Not applicable

