PART B — RS MATH BUGS (verified against approved Epinephrine TSR)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Bug 1 (Critical) — Overage multiplier wrong for injections:
AI uses multiplier = MDD / api_qty = 8/1.1 = 7.2727. Approved uses 
multiplier = 8 (volume-based, ignores 10% overage).

Root cause: strength "1.1 mg/mL" includes 10% API overage. MDD "8 mg/day" is 
nominal label dose. Volume-dosed injection multiplier = mL/day directly, not 
derived from MDD ÷ strength.

Fix in single_strength_unit_composition mode:
Add overage detection during API row analysis:
- If footnote/note contains "overage of API", "10% overage", or similar
- Or if strength has trailing marker "*" or footnote reference indicating overage
- Detect overage_factor (typical 1.10 for 10%, 1.05 for 5%)

For overage products, adjust MDD input UI:
- Ask user: "Is API strength inclusive of overage?" (Yes/No)
- If Yes, ask overage percentage (default 10%)
- Recompute multiplier ignoring overage:
    effective_api_qty_per_unit = api_qty_per_unit / (1 + overage_pct)
    multiplier = MDD / effective_api_qty_per_unit

For volume-dosed liquids (mg/mL basis with mL/day MDD input):
    multiplier = mL/day directly, regardless of overage

Epinephrine test: api_qty=1.10, overage=10%, effective=1.00, MDD volume=8 mL 
→ multiplier=8 (matches approved). Component amounts:
- Epinephrine: 1.10 × 8 = 8.8 mg = 0.0088 g
- Sodium Chloride: 7.5 × 8 = 60 mg = 0.06 g
- Chlorobutanol: 5.25 × 8 = 42 mg = 0.042 g

Bug 2 (Critical) — Drug Product mass wrong for liquid formulations:
AI shows Drug Product mass = 104.36 mg (sum of dissolved solids × 7.27).
Approved: 8800 mg = 8 mL × 1.0 g/mL × 1000. Off by 84×.
Downstream: all equivalent ppm values ~70× wrong.

Fix in drug_product_mass calculation:
Detection rule for liquid dosage:
If quantity_column contains "mg/mL", "mg/ml", or "per mL" (case-insensitive):
    drug_product_mass_mg = mL_per_day × density_g_per_mL × 1000
Default density = 1.0 g/mL for aqueous injection/oral suspension. User override.
Do NOT sum dissolved solids for liquid dosage forms.

Solid dosage (mg/tab, mg/vial, mg/capsule, mg/sachet):
    drug_product_mass = sum of non-q.s. component amounts (existing behavior)

